cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on quality assurance and bug detection in configurable software systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper specifically addresses feature interaction bugs, which are related to the configuration of the software, suggesting that the paper may also fit under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The use of prioritization techniques and sampling algorithms to narrow down the number of configurations to analyze suggests that the paper may also fit under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The evaluation of the proposed technique using experiments suggests that the paper may also fit under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the focus on fault-based configuration prioritization suggests that the paper may also fit under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
